    • Method Detail

      • addRow

        void addRow(java.util.List<java.lang.String> row)
        Adds a new row to a table with the given values. There must be a table open in the builder and the row must have the correct number of values.
        Parameters:
        row - String entries to add to the open table
        Pre-Conditions:
        row != null, row.size() == table width in columns, builder has started table
        Post-Conditions:
        current table has entries from row

      • print

        void print(java.lang.String filename)
        Creates a file containing the content added in the file filename. If the given filename already exists, no report will be created.
        Parameters:
        filename - Location to create the report
        Pre-Conditions:
        ReportBuilder has content added, filename is not already in use
        Post-Conditions:
        A new file is created at filename

      • startTable

        void startTable(java.util.List<java.lang.String> headers)
        Starts new table with headers using the given List values as the header row for the new table. If a table is already started, it will close the current table and open a new one.
        Parameters:
        headers - first row of the table contianing description headers.
        Pre-Conditions:
        headers != null
        Post-Conditions:
        table open with width in columns = headers.size

      • startTable

        void startTable(java.lang.String title,
              java.util.List<java.lang.String> headers)
        Starts new table with headers using the given List values as the header row for the new table, and the title placed above the table. If a table is already started, it will close the current table and open a new one.
        Parameters:
        title - Title to be printed as name for the table
        headers - first row of the table contianing description headers.
        Pre-Conditions:
        headers != null, title != null
        Post-Conditions:
        table open with width in columns = headers.size
